12 April was announced as the 'National Day of Action' last Friday, during the 'Anti Zuma' marches that took place nationwide.Mzansi's political opposition parties call on South Africans to gather for mass protest on the day, which also falls on President Jacob Zuma's birthday.The president will be turning 75 on Wednesday, 12 April.&nbsp;Watch the video as political opposition parties brief the media on National Day of Action taking place on Wednesday:&nbsp;